WEBVTT

00:00.211 --> 00:02.911
<i>My name is Michael Westen.</i>
<i>I used to be a spy until...</i>

00:04.295 --> 00:06.830
We got a burn notice
on you. You're blacklisted.

00:06.897 --> 00:09.265
<i>When you're burned,</i>
<i>you've got nothing --</i>

00:09.333 --> 00:14.137
<i>no cash, no credit,</i>
<i>no job history.</i>

00:14.205 --> 00:16.338
- <i>Where am I?</i>
- <i>Miami.</i>

00:16.407 --> 00:19.509
<i>You do whatever work</i>
<i>comes your way.</i>

00:19.577 --> 00:22.145
<i>You rely on anyone</i>
<i>who's still talking to you.</i>

00:22.213 --> 00:23.747
<i>A trigger-happy</i>
<i>ex-girlfriend...</i>

00:23.814 --> 00:25.382
Should we shoot them?

00:25.449 --> 00:27.984
<i>...An old friend who used</i>
<i>to inform on you to the FBI...</i>

00:28.052 --> 00:30.353
You know spies --
a bunch of bitchy little girls.

00:30.421 --> 00:32.822
<i>...Family, too...</i>
<i>Hey, is that your mom again?</i>

00:32.890 --> 00:35.058
<i>...If you're desperate.</i>
<i>Someone needs your help, Michael.</i>

00:35.126 --> 00:37.560
<i>Bottom line --</i>
<i>as long as you're burned,</i>

00:37.628 --> 00:39.229
<i>you're not going anywhere.</i>

00:45.090 --> 00:47.391
Mr. Westen, we're aware
of your past affiliation

00:47.459 --> 00:49.960
with a rogue network
of burned spies.

00:50.028 --> 00:50.941
To the best
of your knowledge,

00:50.966 --> 00:53.027
does any trace of that network
still exist.

00:53.398 --> 00:54.598
No.

00:56.368 --> 00:58.536
All of that's over now.

01:00.338 --> 01:01.438
Who the hell are you?

01:01.506 --> 01:02.873
I'm the one
who watched you tear down

01:02.941 --> 01:05.910
every last shred of the
organization that burned you.

01:05.977 --> 01:07.912
The organization I spent
half my life building.

01:10.081 --> 01:11.348
I framed you,

01:11.416 --> 01:13.083
and now I'm framing
your girlfriend for murder.

01:13.151 --> 01:14.451
I own you.

01:14.519 --> 01:16.387
I don't want you doing anything
for that man.

01:16.454 --> 01:17.888
I don't have a choice, Fi,

01:17.956 --> 01:19.223
unless we find some leverage
of our own.

01:19.291 --> 01:20.457
Michael, listen to me.

01:20.525 --> 01:22.426
There's no moves left
on the chess board.

01:22.494 --> 01:23.761
I know you.

01:23.828 --> 01:25.696
About five years ago,
I filled in

01:25.764 --> 01:27.531
as a substitute
for Madeline's therapist.

01:27.599 --> 01:28.933
She didn't know
who she was talking to.

01:29.000 --> 01:31.835
It's your father
you <i>should</i> be upset with.

01:31.903 --> 01:34.071
The things <i>that</i> man gave us
before he passed away...

01:34.139 --> 01:36.640
Anson's using that dish
to talk to someone.

01:36.708 --> 01:38.409
So, Anson
was calling here?

01:38.476 --> 01:40.411
- Wait a second. Is that...
- Benny.

01:40.478 --> 01:42.246
As in, your mother's
boyfriend, Benny.

01:45.317 --> 01:46.850
Ma,
you don't have to do this.

01:46.918 --> 01:47.952
I don't care
how long it takes.

01:48.019 --> 01:49.787
I want to know
if it was all a lie.

01:49.854 --> 01:51.388
Did you get
the package I sent you?

01:51.456 --> 01:52.389
<i>Yeah,</i>
<i>I got the package.</i>

01:52.457 --> 01:53.757
Package?

02:00.999 --> 02:03.434
<i>When a spy is killed</i>
<i>in the field,</i>

02:03.501 --> 02:06.437
<i>it's often hardest on the</i>
<i>people they were spying on.</i>

02:06.504 --> 02:07.771
It's about Benny.

02:07.839 --> 02:09.872
Anson is using him
to spy on us.

02:09.941 --> 02:12.076
<i>Mourning the death of someone</i>
<i>you thought you knew</i>

02:12.143 --> 02:13.677
<i>is complicated enough</i>

02:13.745 --> 02:15.913
<i>when the spy was</i>
<i>a trusted colleague or friend.</i>

02:15.981 --> 02:17.748
I thought
he had feelings for me.

02:17.816 --> 02:19.550
<i>But it's even more difficult</i>

02:19.618 --> 02:21.485
<i>when they were someone</i>
<i>you loved.</i>

